<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="335" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1157,662,1728]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,268,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baqri QH" box="[285,421,663,688]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref18088" refString="Baqri QH. 1991. Contribution to the fauna of Sikkim. Nematodes associated with citrus from Sikkim, India. Records of the zoological survey of India. Occas Pap. 128: 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1991">Baqri (1991)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baqri" authorityYear="1991" box="[547,676,663,688]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mujtabai">
<emphasis box="[547,676,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. mujtabai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[746,822,663,688]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[833,891,663,688]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">India</collectingCountry>
. The morphometrics of the present specimens conform well with the 
<typeStatus box="[678,728,698,723]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">type</typeStatus>
specimens except in having a slightly shorter male body (L = 0.64 vs 
<quantity box="[509,608,732,757]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="0.75">0.75 mm</quantity>
) and shorter odontophore (12–14 vs 15–16 µm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1157,662,1728]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">
<bibRefCitation author="Gambhir RK &amp; Anandi Y &amp; Dhanachand C" box="[192,435,767,792]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref18422" refString="Gambhir RK, Anandi Y, Dhanachand C. 1997. Soil nematodes from Manipur III. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936 (Mydonomidae: Dorylaimida). Utt Pra J Zool. 17: 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1997">Gambhir et al. (1997)</bibRefCitation>
described two new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[770,896,767,792]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="musasus">
<emphasis box="[770,896,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. musasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1150,767,792]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="microspicoides">
<emphasis box="[958,1150,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. microspicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion box="[223,320,802,827]" country="India" name="Manipur" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Manipur</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[332,390,802,827]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">India</collectingCountry>
. Some doubts persist regarding the true identity of these species, because the original description lacks some relevant details. They (l.c.) differentiated 
<taxonomicName box="[160,352,871,896]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="microspicoides">
<emphasis box="[160,352,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. microspicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[425,551,871,896]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="musasus">
<emphasis box="[425,551,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. musasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based only on the shorter odontostyle (ventral arm 6.0–7.0 vs 8.0–10 µm, dorsal arm 8.0–9.0 vs 8.0–10 µm) and odontophore (8.0–10 vs 11– 13 µm), smaller b (4.5–4.7 vs 4.9–6.6) and c (19–23 vs 18–20) ratios, shorter rectum (9.0–13 vs 16 µm) and presence of male (vs male absent). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Gambhir RK &amp; Anandi Y &amp; Dhanachand C" box="[871,1107,975,1000]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref18422" refString="Gambhir RK, Anandi Y, Dhanachand C. 1997. Soil nematodes from Manipur III. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936 (Mydonomidae: Dorylaimida). Utt Pra J Zool. 17: 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1997">Gambhir et al. (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, the two arms of the odontostyle are equal (9.0–10 µm, 8.0–10 µm) in 
<taxonomicName box="[912,1036,1010,1035]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="musasus">
<emphasis box="[912,1036,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. musasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and both arms of the odontostyle are almost the same length in the two species (8.0–10 vs 8.0– 9.0 µm) whereas they differ slightly in the length of the ventral arm (6.0–7.0 vs 8.0–10 µm). These unusual differences create some doubts about the validity of these species, because the dorsal arm is always longer than the ventral arm in all 
<taxonomicName box="[907,1156,1149,1174]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[907,1062,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Dorylaimoides</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
The figures (figs 1(b) and 2(b) of 
<bibRefCitation author="Gambhir RK &amp; Anandi Y &amp; Dhanachand C" box="[565,802,1183,1208]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref18422" refString="Gambhir RK, Anandi Y, Dhanachand C. 1997. Soil nematodes from Manipur III. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936 (Mydonomidae: Dorylaimida). Utt Pra J Zool. 17: 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1997">Gambhir et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
) do not correspond with the morphometric values given in their paper, and there seem to be some errors either in their measurements or in the scales used.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1157,662,1728]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">
Morphometrically as well as morphologically, 
<taxonomicName box="[704,826,1287,1312]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="musasus">
<emphasis box="[704,826,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. musasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[882,1071,1287,1312]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="microspicoides">
<emphasis box="[882,1071,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. microspicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear very close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Baqri, 1991" authorityName="Baqri" authorityYear="1991" box="[308,567,1322,1347]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mujtabai">
<emphasis box="[308,436,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. mujtabai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baqri QH" box="[443,567,1322,1347]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref18088" refString="Baqri QH. 1991. Contribution to the fauna of Sikkim. Nematodes associated with citrus from Sikkim, India. Records of the zoological survey of India. Occas Pap. 128: 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1991">Baqri, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, their morphometric values widely overlapping with the latter. It is interesting to note that these species were not compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baqri" authorityYear="1991" box="[1028,1155,1357,1382]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mujtabai">
<emphasis box="[1028,1155,1357,1382]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. mujtabai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the original description. There is every possibility that they are conspecific to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baqri" authorityYear="1991" box="[160,288,1426,1451]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mujtabai">
<emphasis box="[160,288,1426,1451]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D. mujtabai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1157,662,1728]" lastBlockId="24.[160,1156,142,341]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="335" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">
<bibRefCitation author="Baqri QH &amp; Jairajpuri MS" box="[192,504,1461,1486]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="408 - 424" refId="ref18126" refString="Baqri QH, Jairajpuri MS. 1969. Morasia n. gen. and three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936 (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea) from India. Nematologica. 15 (3): 408 - 424. doi: 10.1163 / 187529269 X 00498." type="journal article" year="1969">Baqri and Jairajpuri (1969)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baqri &amp; Jairajpuri" authorityYear="1969" box="[824,1015,1461,1486]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="arcuicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[824,847,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">D.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3819589304" box="[859,1015,1461,1486]" country="India" location="Uttar Pradesh" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Uttar Pradesh">
<emphasis box="[859,1015,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">arcuicaudatus</emphasis>
</materialsCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion country="India" name="Uttar Pradesh" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Uttar Pradesh</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[268,327,1495,1520]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">India</collectingCountry>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3819589309" country="India" location="West Bengal" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-female="1" stateProvince="West Bengal">
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" box="[342,600,1495,1520]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri (1981)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed this species based on 
<specimenCount box="[1023,1156,1495,1520]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[348,490,1530,1555]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[501,559,1530,1555]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">India</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3819589305" collectorName="Some" country="India" location="West Bengal" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="West Bengal">
<collectorName box="[570,633,1530,1555]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Some</collectorName>
doubts exist about the correct identity of the 
<collectingRegion box="[160,304,1565,1590]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
population as it shows some major morphometric differences including a shorter and robust body (L = 0.68–0.75 vs 
<quantity box="[678,813,1599,1624]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.4 mm</quantity>
, a = 25–27 vs 31–36), shorter odontophore (12–14 vs 15–16 µm), lower b (4.7–5.2 vs 7.1–8.4) and c (18–20 vs 27–29) ratios and shorter prerectum (49–55 vs 110–117 µm)
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3819589307" collectorName="Peralta &amp; Pena-Santiago" country="India" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="335" location="West Bengal" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="West Bengal">
<collectorName box="[777,854,1669,1694]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Peralta</collectorName>
and 
<collectorName box="[915,1077,1669,1694]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">Peña-Santiago</collectorName>
(1997) also commented on the 
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" box="[436,678,1703,1728]" pageId="23" pageNumber="334" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri (1981)</bibRefCitation>
population and did not consider the 
<collectingRegion country="India" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="335" name="West Bengal" pageId="23" pageNumber="334">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
population conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baqri &amp; Jairajpuri" authorityYear="1969" box="[565,584,142,167]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="arcuicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[565,584,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">D</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
<emphasis box="[584,748,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">. arcuicaudatus</emphasis>
. The morphometrics of this population is quite comparable to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Baqri (1991)" authorityName="Baqri" authorityYear="1991" box="[578,859,177,202]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mujtabai">
<emphasis box="[578,710,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">D. mujtabai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baqri QH" box="[720,859,177,202]" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref18088" refString="Baqri QH. 1991. Contribution to the fauna of Sikkim. Nematodes associated with citrus from Sikkim, India. Records of the zoological survey of India. Occas Pap. 128: 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1991">Baqri (1991)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Taking into account this evidence, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jana and Baqri, 1981" authorityName="Jana and Baqri" authorityYear="1981" box="[285,829,212,237]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" phylum="Nematoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arcuicaudatus" subSpecies="apud">
<emphasis box="[285,553,212,237]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">D. arcuicaudatus apud</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" box="[568,829,212,237]" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is considered identical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baqri" authorityYear="1991" box="[160,288,246,271]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mujtabai">
<emphasis box="[160,288,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">D. mujtabai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,142,341]" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">
The present population also conforms well with the 
<collectingRegion box="[772,910,281,306]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="24" pageNumber="335">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
population described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" box="[195,423,316,341]" pageId="24" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri 1981</bibRefCitation>
except in having a slightly longer prerectum (62–84 vs 49–55).
</paragraph>
